# Developer Sign-off

By adding a `Signed-off-by` line to your commits, you certify that:

1. You wrote the contribution or have the right to submit it under the MIT License
2. You understand the contribution will be public and distributed under the MIT License
3. You're okay with your name and email being included in the project history

That's it! Just use `git commit -s` and you're good to go.
